{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the contributions of this paper can be summarized as follows:",
    "We propose TCN-ECANet-GRU, which is a newer method for predicting short-term PV power values.",
    "This approach represents a relatively new attempt in the field and may also be used for other time series forecasting. 2.",
    "The proposed TCN-ECANet-GRU model uses a temporal convolutional network for spatial feature learning from multiple time series to capture temporal and spatial features; on this basis, ECANet is used to improve the performance of TCNs to expand the sensory field of TCNs for better feature capture and prediction. 3.",
    "The performance of the proposed TCN-ECANet-GRU method in terms of single-step prediction and multistep prediction is demonstrated based on a case study of a real PV power generation dataset, where the RMSE, MAE and R 2 are used as evaluation metrics."
  ]
}